The two were reportedly sleeping in the shrubbery when they were hit by a car on the N1 Highway in Cape Town. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating the deaths of two people in a crash on the N1 Highway in Cape Town.The incident took place on Saturday when a vehicle veered off the road into vegetation separating the incoming and outgoing lanes.It's understood the homeless people had been sleeping in the shrubbery when they were hit by the car.ER24's Annine Doormel says the driver believed to be in her 70's had apparently blacked out. ER24 paramedics came across the scene and declared two men dead on the scene. One man believed to be between 30 and 40 years of age was lucky to escape with minor injuries and the driver sustained minor injuries on her forehead. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)